Like, we know these predators are human, we know how their art impacted this world. The problem is how much power certain industries give human beings. We can't simply ignore the harm they cause, when their power directly comes from the art, from OUR CONSUMPTION.
We need to stop centering these abusers/bigots/predators. Stop giving them grace, and figure out ways we can let go of the memories their art influences.

I refuse to give these artists grace. I wish we could all divest, but the fact of the matter is many cannot because of the impact of THE ART, not the ARTIST. We(because I have this struggle as well) cannot divest from the memories, intimate ways some of this art impacted us.

The artist vs. art argument is so nuanced but because of the way their capital, and power to harm comes from the very art we all consume. The argument should never be about their humanity, but ours as consumers, and how art impacts our lives, and our struggle with detaching.
